title: Meet Gudetama, the dessert that vomits custard and poos chocolate just because
text:
And everyone wants to end their meal with a tiny cartoon character vomiting and sh*tting, right?
Sanrio, the company behind Hello Kitty as well as other various cartoon characters in Asia, recently opened a pop-up cafe in Hong Kong themed around their 'laziest' character ' Gudetama ' who is some sort of weird egg yolk character that does nothing other than lie around in his/her egg white asking to not be disturbed.
Now all of this makes sense in terms of a restaurant that could serve up egg-based meals but egg for dessert was always going to be a hard sell. Enter the sweet Gudetama Dim Sum.
The custard vomit option is equally impressive.
Appetizing, no?
Via Kotaku
